{"url": "https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/10/15/saturday-night-live-finally-tackles-harvey-weinstein-scandal-harassment-hollywood/759900001/", "text": "'Saturday Night Live' finally tackles the Harvey Weinstein scandal, harassment in Hollywood\n\nCLOSE Saturday Night Live's Kate McKinnon makes Kellyanne Conway a scary clown, while the show weighs in on the Harvey Weinstein scandal.\n\nAfter initially side-stepping the Harvey Weinstein scandal, Saturday Night Live stepped up to address the issue this weekend.\n\nLeslie Jones as Viola Davis, Cecily Strong as Marion Cotillard and Kate McKinnon as Debette Goldry on 'SNL.' (Photo: Will Heath, NBC)\n\nIn light of the allegations that Weinstein sexually assaulted and sexually harassed more than a dozen women, Leslie Jones\u2019 Viola Davis, Cecily Strong\u2019s Marion Cotillard and Kate McKinnon\u2019s no-holds-barred Debette Goldry held a roundtable to discuss their experiences with sexual predation in the film industry.\n\n\"Having a lady in the family doesn\u2019t make you some kind of hero!\" #SNLpic.twitter.com/3gz9EUoC5H \u2014 Saturday Night Live (@nbcsnl) October 15, 2017\n\n\u201cHave I ever experienced sexual harassment in Hollywood? Good Friday, where do you want me to start?\u201d Goldry exclaimed. \u201cWomen being harassed is Hollywood. Everything old is new again. Producers are abusing starlets. There\u2019s Nazis marching in the street. And suddenly nude pantyhose are on-trend. I have never felt more at home.\u201d\n\nThe allegations against Harvey Weinstein prompted a lot of reflection about harassment in Hollywood. #SNLpic.twitter.com/z98AeNV2tN \u2014 Saturday Night Live (@nbcsnl) October 15, 2017\n\nLater, Goldry called out Weinstein directly: \u201cI actually did have one meeting with Harvey. I was invited to his hotel room. When I arrived, he was naked hanging upside down from a monkey bar. Tried to trick me into thinking his genitals were actually his face. It almost worked. The resemblance is uncanny.\u201d\n\nRELATED: Kate McKinnon's Kellyanne Conway Is \u2018It\u2019 \u2013 and not in a good way\n\nMcKinnon\u2019s Goldry wasn\u2019t the only one with extraneous jokes about Weinstein\u2019s appearance. \"Weekend Update\" star Michael Che also cracked, \u201cIt\u2019s so hard to make jokes about sexual assault, but so easy to make jokes about a guy who looks like this. I mean, he looks like chewed-up bubblegum rolled in cat hair.\u201d\n\nFor his part, Che\u2019s co-anchor Colin Jost remained on-topic: \u201cHe needs a specialized facility where there are no women, no contact with the outside world, metal bars \u2013 and it\u2019s a prison.\u201d\n\nRead or Share this story: https://usat.ly/2wWCSba", "images": ["https://www.gannett-cdn.com/uxstatic/usatoday/usat-web-static-5005.62.0/images/social-icons/comments-copy.png", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/sites/usatoday/images/site-nav-logo-dark@2x.png", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/uxstatic/usatoday/usat-web-static-5005.62.0/images/sprites/icon_close.png", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/uxstatic/usatoday/usat-web-static-5005.62.0/images/indicators/facebook-loading.gif", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/uxstatic/usatoday/usat-web-static-5005.62.0/images/social-icons/oval-1-facebook.png", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2019/04/15/USAT/ce53f38b-3d6d-4c7b-a9b4-c95a782ad3b6-Spidey_MJ.jpg?crop=2264,2264,x694,y248&width=60&height=60&fit=bounds", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/sites/usatoday/images/site-masthead-logo-dark@2x.png", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/uxstatic/usatoday/usat-web-static-5005.62.0/images/social-icons/oval-1-copy-twitter.png", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/5be533b042ff583fa288d340d7cea9a86748e7ab/c=0-0-2999-1694/local/-/media/2017/10/15/USATODAY/USATODAY/636436508139688551-NUP-180310-0038.JPG?width=580&height=326&fit=crop", "https://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/5be533b042ff583fa288d340d7cea9a86748e7ab/c=0-0-2999-1694/local/-/media/2017/10/15/USATODAY/USATODAY/636436508139688551-NUP-